Argentine Stocks: Ledesma SAAI, MetroGAS SA Increase

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-06-08T16:28:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/argentine-stocks-ledesma-saai-metrogas-sa-increase.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:08 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index rose 0.4 percent to 3,138.22.  Ledesma SAAI (LEDE AF), the Argentine sugar producer,
gained 3.9 percent to 7.90 pesos, as the sweetener advanced for
the fourth time in five sessions on speculation that Brazilian
output may be lower than previously expected.  Brazil  is the
world’s largest sugar producer. Raw sugar for July delivery
increased 0.74 cent, or 3 percent, to 25.09 cents a pound in New
York.  MetroGAS SA (METR)  ,  Argentina ’s largest natural gas
distributor, advanced 3.4 percent to 1.22 pesos. Shares have
gained 30 percent since June 2 when BG Group Plc agreed to sell
its 54.6 percent stake in Metrogas to YPF SA. El Cronista
Comercial yesterday reported that Marcelo Mindlin, chief
executive officer of Pampa Energia SA, may seek to acquire the
stake from YPF by swapping defaulted Metrogas debt he holds for
equity. The newspaper cited people it didn’t identify.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in  New York  at 
 llazaroff@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
